          },
          "datePublished": "2024-05-28",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Unprofessional behavior of admin staff. No one picking call on admin reception. no one even bother to give response on email. Especially Darshan mam' in admin department, she keeps shouting if parent reach directly to school as no response of email or call.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Navrachana International School - Bhayli"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Meghna Shah"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-04-29",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Doesn't deserve even a 1 star..if u have moved from a metro city, then will realize it is just an overly hyped school locally,  with zero quality in education,  sports selection only fr selected few students,except for few faculties ,rest are just average teachers,  The staff especially the principal is very partial towards affluent parents, we spent 2 precious  years of our children here after moving from a metro city n all we have is just regrets..If parents want to be in a circle of the who's and who's of baroda and boast abt their economic standards then this school is the best but if u want to secure child's future by focus on education and also better infrastructure then there are better options around which are less popular but really maintain quality in education.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
